      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-08T21:06:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is only sized appropriately if the target process is 32-bit. It\u0027s possible that the tracer will be 32-bit while the target process is 64-bit. The other architectures pass in the ThreadContext, which is large enough for either 32 or 64 bit, and use the iov.iov_len returned by the kernel to interpret it appropriately. If you wanted to use the same strategy, the ThreadContext::t32 struct would need to have this layout. It\u0027s a little annoying that then you wouldn\u0027t be able to re-use it for the SignalThreadContext, but I think that\u0027s probably a small price to make this code simpler.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 355,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 374,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "7c6d7190e9034e96e732726ec47734798aa04c9a",
